<font color="#FF0000">RESPONSE TO BETTY</font><br>
<tt>Wed Apr 16 20:17:34 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Betty,<br><br>
I am truly moved by your comments and sincerely appreciate them. Many Vietnam Veterans, such as myself, are out on the internet looking for understanding and an appreciation for our points of view. We lived this history, and for many of us the history, the experience, continues to live on inside because we are, quite simply, human.<br><br>
Many of us have lost, or more hopefully misplaced, those tenuous threads that bind us to the world at large. I found here some of the threads I misplaced a long time ago. Some call it healing. I call it feeling alive, once again.<br><br>
Controversy will always surround the Vietnam Experience. It is a vortex of events, emotions, philosophy, misdirected ambition, disasterous leadership, and all the ills of a human legacy. In situations such as these, extremes abound, never a middle ground. You see here, on this site, a glimpse of our experience of extremes, extremes that we act out in words for all the world to see. That is what is truly important. Opinions, strong words, epithets, come and go behind a thin veil of reality. That our words are here, and here and now, is the manifest reality for some of our connections back into life.<br><br>
Please continue with your comments, and Thanks! 
<p><code>-- art16@ix.netcom.com  (Arthur Varanelli) </code><p>


